<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-02T09:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-02T09:44:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-02T14:00:00-00:44">March 2,
                                    1942—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 2:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>52. From McBride.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>First plane arrived yesterday overnighted at Harbel. Pilot
                                enthusiastic about landing field. Some difficulty encountered
                                because of fadeouts but radio contact Harbel to Accra for plane
                                direction finally established.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Obtained permission from Liberian Government February 17 for
                                Harbel radio station to communicate directly with Fisherman Lake and
                                other necessary points. Such communication to be exclusively for
                                direction of plane traffic. This permission, which is outside their
                                contract, granted to the Firestone station only temporarily until
                                Panair can establish its own radio facilities at air field. This
                                latter should be given prompt attention. [McBride.]</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>